    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note No. 1271 of the 25th instant respecting the ordinances of Trinidad and
                    Tobago, and the necessary action to be taken by the President, toward the
                    revocation of the former proclamations, in consequence of the imposition of
                    taxes imposed on American vessels by the government of the island of
                    Trinidad.</p>
                <p>I shall not fail to bring your courteous note to the immediate attention of Her
                    Majesty’s Government, and shall be pleased to convey to you the reply I may
                    receive thereto.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
